      "amount": "to taste"
    },
    {
      "name": "Ground Black Pepper",
      "amount": "to taste"
    }
  ],
  "instructions": [
    "Preheat oven to 375°F (190°C).",
    "Slice bread into ¼-inch thick pieces.",
    "In a large bowl, combine bread slices, Saskatoon berries, olive oil, garlic, parsley, salt, and pepper. Mix gently until the bread is evenly coated with the berry mixture.",
    "Spread the crumbled mixture onto prepared baking sheets lined with parchment paper.",
    "Bake for 20-25 minutes or until golden brown on top and crisp. Stir occasionally during cooking to ensure even browning.",
    "Remove from oven, let cool slightly before serving."
  ],
